               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Gadla Mazgaba Śǝllāse “Vita of Mazgaba Śǝllāse” (fols. 5ra-66ra)
                     II) Taʾammǝra Mazgaba Śǝllāse “Miracles of Mazgaba Śǝllāse – 14 miracles (fols.
                     66rb-76vb)
 III) Mälkǝʾa Mazgaba Śǝllāse “Image of Mazgaba Śǝllāse” (fols.
                     77ra-79ra)
 IV) Salām-hymn for Mazgaba Śǝllāse (fols. 79ra-79rb)
 
                     Colophon.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                     <colophon xml:id="coloph1">
                        <locus target="#79va">79va</locus>, l.1: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘታቦተ፡ መዝገበ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ወደብረ፡ ብርሃን፡
                        ቅድስት፡ ማርያም፡ ፈቃዳ፡ ዘወሀቦ፡ አቶ፡ መዝገቦ፡ አጽብሐ፡ ይኩኖ፡ መርሕ፡ ለመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ምስለ፡ ኵሉ፡ ስብአ፡
                        ቤቱ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም። በ፲፻ወ፱፻፺ወ፮፡ ዓ[መተ]፡ ም [ሕረት]፡ በዘመነ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ወንጌላዊ። ወጸሐፌ፡ ዝንቱ፡ መ፡ ሕደ፡
                        ገ፡ ማ፡ ዘብ፡ ልገት። Mention of the name of the donor, Mazgaba ʾAṣbǝḥa, the date,
                        1996 A.M. (= 2003/04 A.D.), and the abbreviated name of the scribe, Gabra
                        Māryām (?) of Legät (also known as Lǝgat). </colophon>
                  </msItem>
                  
               </msContents>
